<article>
    <h1>SOUND SO&#xAD;CIAL SERIES</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201204/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-04"><time>2020-12-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Sin­ga­pore In­ter­na­tional Fes­ti­val Of Arts’ v2.020 pro­gramme puts the spot­light on home-grown artists who are mak­ing their mark in the sound art scene through the Sound So­cial Series.</p>
    <p>Over three Wed­nes­days in De­cem­ber, the per­for­mances will take place both live and on­line as video-on-de­mand streams.</p>
    <p>Catch En­tity, elec­tronic pro­ducer and sound artist Planeswalk­er’s hal­lu­ci­na­tory au­dio-vis­ual per­for­mances, on Dec 9.</p>
    <p>Of Na­ture And Tech­nol­ogy, a work by The Straits Times Life Theatre Award win­ner and sound artist Zul Mah­mod, fea­tures sound sculp­tures made with drift­woods found in Sin­ga­pore. It takes place on Dec 16.</p>
    <p>The third per­for­mance on Dec 23 is a col­lab­o­ra­tion be­tween singer-song­writer and one half of elec­tronic duo .gif, Weish (above), and vis­ual artist and de­signer Marc Gabriel Loh.</p>
    <p>WHERE Live per­for­mances at Black Box, Good­man Arts Cen­tre, 90 Good­man Road MRT Mount­bat­ten WHEN Dec 9 to 29, var­i­ous times AD­MIS­SION $15 for live per­for­mances; $10, $15 and $20 for video-on-de­mand. Tick­ets sold through Sis­tic (www.sis­tic.com.sg) INFO bit.ly/33CYpYq</p>

